.TH "ssam_request_sync" 9 "ssam_request_sync" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ssam_request_sync \- Execute a synchronous request.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ssam_request_sync
.BI "(struct ssam_controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "const struct ssam_request *spec "  ","
.BI "struct ssam_response *rsp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
The controller via which the request will be submitted.
.IP "spec" 12
The request specification and payload.
.IP "rsp" 12
The response buffer.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocates a synchronous request with its message data buffer on the heap
via \fBssam_request_sync_alloc\fP, fully initializes it via the provided
request specification, submits it, and finally waits for its completion
before freeing it and returning its status.
.SH "RETURN"
Returns the status of the request or any failure during setup.
